# Production Environment Configuration Template
# Copy these settings to your hosting platform's environment variables

# Essential Production Settings
NODE_ENV=production
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secure-jwt-secret-here-make-it-long-and-random
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/database-name
FRONT_END_URL=https://your-frontend-domain.com

# Optional Settings
PORT=3001

# Instructions:
# 1. Generate a new JWT_SECRET using: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(64).toString('hex'))"
# 2. Replace FRONT_END_URL with your actual frontend domain (no trailing slash)
# 3. Update MONGO_URI with your production database credentials
# 4. Ensure both frontend and backend are deployed with HTTPS